			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">specialization 50 = 3%
<br />
specialization 200 = 11%
<br />

<br />
SCM1 = 2%
<br />
SCM2 = 5%
<br />
SCM3 = 10%
<br />

<br />
To get the mana saved add up the modifiers.  An alter spec nec with SCM3 will save 21% on alteration spells, 13% on the rest.
<br />

<br />
Focus modifiers are added at the same time.  So an alter spec nec with SCM3 and Preservation of Xegony will save 11+10+8 = 29% on alteration spells. (8 on PoX since it's 1-15% or 8% average)
<br />

<br />
Source here: <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=23.topic" target="_blank">http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=23.topic</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
